        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 15 at 4:18PM CDT by NWS Birmingham AL</headline>
        <description>At 418 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Verbena, or near Clanton, moving southeast at 15 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects.

Locations impacted include...
Clanton, Thorsby, Mitchell Lake, Higgins Ferry Park, Verbena, Lomax,
I 65 Rest Area, Mitchell Dam, and Cooper.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
